Having thus reckoned up ſome heads of Impertinencies, I cannot eaſily imagine any other cauſe why our Author ſhould patch up Hippocrates his ſleeve, with pieces and patterns of all ſorts of ſtuff, unleſs he had been ambitious of a Party-coloured Coat, to have ſomething of every thing in his Book, with this Motto, Omne tulit punctum. But he may call to mind theſe two Verſes;


Grammaticus, Rhetor, Geometres, Pictor, Aliptes:

Dum dubitas quid ſis, jam potis eſſe nihil.

